OL,5, A "fantasist" killer who assumed the   
OL,6, identity of a dead man who had the same
OL,7, name as him has been has been found    
OL,8, guilty of murder some 39 years later.  
OL,10,FPaul Bryan was 22 when he stabbed      
OL,11,F62-year-old Roman Szalajko at the      
OL,12,Fvictim's south London home in 1984.    
OL,14,FThe Old Bailey heard the crime remained
OL,15,Funsolved as Bryan, now aged 62, "simply
OL,16,Fdisappeared" by assuming a false       
OL,17,Fidentity and moving abroad.            
OL,19,FThe Met unlocked the mystery after     
OL,20,Flaunching a cold case review in 2013.  
